This paper deals with the problem of signal classification in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The use of deep learning techniques for signal classification suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the issue of interference from jammers, which is a security concern and may place the paper under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses blind source separation using independent component analysis, which is a technique commonly used in signal processing and may place the paper under the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT).
